  "texts": [
    "However, we can reuse some of the computations by storing the quantities S s,p =2 m-s l=0 |y p•2 m-s +l | 2 ina binary-tree data structure with m levels [3].",
    "The tree has 2 m-1 leaves; we store the quantities S m-1,p in the leaves for p = 0,..., 2 m-1 -1.",
    "The tree is then constructed recursively by the rule that a parent stores the sum of its children.",
    "Since S s,p = S s+1,2p + S s+1,2p+1, we can verify that the value of the p th node at level s will store the value S s,p.",
    "The angle θ s,p can then be determined only from the values stored at this node along with its two children."
  ],
